The search and rescue operation for the second man has been stopped due to the weather. JOHANNESBURG - The body of an illegal miner has been found in a disused Riverlea mine where it s believed another so-called zama zama is still trapped.The police's Kay Makhubela says the body was found yesterday afternoon. Makhubela says the search and rescue operation for the second man has been stopped due to the weather. The illegal miners took out the body of one of the illegal miners when they were on site. They called the police and the man was taken to a government mortuary. We have opened a docket of inquest. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)